YENAGOA – A gang of gunmen believed to be kidnappers has abducted Jephthah Robert, a cousin of former President Goodluck Jonathan. Daily Independent gathered that he was kidnapped at 9:30 pm on Tuesday in front of his house around Dimrose Road in Yenagoa. The victim is the elder brother of Azibaola Robert, who is the Founder and Chief Executive Officer of Zeetin Engineering Limited. 2022: God Has Something Special For Bayelsa – Pastor… Another Paramount Ruler Kidnapped In Plateau Though details of Jephthah’s abduction had been sketchy, the Police Public Relations Officer, Bayelsa State Command, SP Asinim Butswat, confirmed the incident. Butswat said,”He was picked up at Dimrose Road in Yenagoa. We are intensifying efforts to rescue him and arrest the kidnappers. “We are working on a promising lead.” No group had claimed responsibility for Jephthah’s abduction even as the motive behind his kidnap b not be ascertained as of the time of filing this report. The abduction of Jonathan’s cousin occurred 24 hours after the state Commissioner for Industry, Trade and Investment, Federal Otokito, was freed by his abductors. POLL Otokito has whisked away from his residence on January 20 in his community, Otuokpoti, in the Ogbia Local Government Area of the state. The commissioner spent about five days in the custody of his assailants before he was released on Monday.